Matteo Larrode

Hi!

Im Matto, I firmly believe that data can drive positive social change, and Im committed to applying my skills to create meaningful impact.

As a data science intern at the British Red Cross, I am contributing to the development of the Health Inequalities Explorer, an open-source web app aimed at aiding decision-making within operational teams at the British Red Cross. This app is enhanced and supported by the humaniverse suite of open-source R packages, which centralises health inequalities data across the UK.

Im also Volunteer Head of Data & Analytics at LEquipage Solidaire, a French non-profit that fights food waste and the cost of living crisis by delivering food and hygienic supplies to needy students at their home, for free. In this role, I lead a team of three data scientists, with the objectives of advocating for data-driven decisions, increasing our transparency, and ensuring an ethical use of data. I am also building an open-source package, packageSolidaire, which is a companion to pre-process our data, and to plot and map deliveries using the visual identity of the charity.

These experiences, along with side projects like this shiny app mapping election results in India, built in collaboration with Emmanuel Teitelbaum, PhD, honed my skills in data storytelling, inferential statistics, and critical thinking. But most of all, they opened my eyes on the importance of translating data into actionable insights.

Having lived in France, London, and Washington D.C., and having worked as a Research Assistant with Dr.Laila Sorurbakhsh, Ive had the chance to meet wonderful friends and mentors, from all around the world. Outside of work and academia, I like to build bikes, play football, climb, and surf!

Thank you for visiting my web page, and please dont hesitate to reach out if you have any questions or would like to learn more about my work.

Education

University College London | London, UK | B.Sc. Politics, Philosophy & Economics w/ Social Data Analysis | September 2020 - May 2024

George Washington University | Washington D.C., USA | Year Abroad | August 2022 - May 2023

Experience

British Red Cross - Strategic Insights & Foresight | Data Scientist (Intern) | July 2023 - Present

Equipage Solidaire | Head of Data & Analytics | January 2023 - Present

Elliott School of IR (GWU) | Washington, D.C. | Research Assistant | August 2022 - May 2023
